𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟓: 𝐆𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧 𝐀𝐥𝐩𝐡𝐚𝐛𝐞𝐭 - ✨
🔠 The German alphabet has 30 letters: 👉 26 English letters
 ➕ ä, ö, ü, and ß

🔍 A few quick tips:
j sounds like “y”
v sounds like “f”
w sounds like “v”
No word starts with ß

🧠 Learning by Example – A bis Z + Ä, Ö, Ü, ß:

A – Apfel – Apple
 B – Brot – Bread
 C – Computer – Computer
 D – Dorf – Village
 E – Eis – Ice Cream
 F – Fisch – Fish
 G – Garten – Garden
 H – Haus – House
 I – Insel – Island
 J – Jahr – Year
 K – Katze – Cat
 L – Lampe – Lamp
 M – Maus – Mouse
 N – Nase – Nose
 O – Ofen – Oven
 P – Pizza – Pizza
 Q – Quelle – Spring / Source
 R – Rose – Rose
 S – Sonne – Sun
 T – Tisch – Table
 U – Uhr – Clock
 V – Vogel – Bird
 W – Wasser – Water
 X – Xylofon – Xylophone
 Y – Yoga – Yoga
 Z – Zucker – Sugar
 Ä – Äpfel – Apples
 Ö – Öl – Oil
 Ü – Über – Over
 ß – Straße – Street

